---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Beit Hamikdash Scale Model">

    <main class="main">

    <!-- Page Title -->
    <div class="page-title">
      <div class="breadcrumbs">
        <nav aria-label="breadcrumb">
          <ol class="breadcrumb">
            <li class="breadcrumb-item"><a href="/"><i class="bi bi-house"></i> Home</a></li>
            <li class="breadcrumb-item"><a href="/portfolio">Portfolio</a></li>
            <li class="breadcrumb-item active current">Beit Hamikdash Scale Model</li>
          </ol>
        </nav>
      </div>

      <div class="container section-title pb-0">
        <h2>Beit Hamikdash Scale Model</h2>
        <div class="title-shape">
          <svg viewBox="0 0 200 20" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">
            <path d="M 0,10 C 40,0 60,20 100,10 C 140,0 160,20 200,10" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"></path>
          </svg>
        </div>
      </div><!-- End Section Title -->
    </div><!-- End Page Title -->

    <!-- Portfolio Details Section -->
    <section id="portfolio-details" class="portfolio-details section">

      <div class="container">

        <div class="row gy-4 g-lg-5">
          <div class="col-lg-6">
            <img src="/assets/img/portfolio/6.webp" class="img-fluid mb-4 rounded-4" alt="" loading="lazy">
            <img src="/assets/img/portfolio/7.webp" class="img-fluid mb-4 rounded-4" alt="" loading="lazy">
            <img src="/assets/img/portfolio/8.webp" class="img-fluid mb-4 rounded-4" alt="" loading="lazy">
            <img src="/assets/img/portfolio/9.webp" class="img-fluid mb-4 rounded-4" alt="" loading="lazy">
            <img src="/assets/img/portfolio/10.webp" class="img-fluid mb-4 rounded-4" alt="" loading="lazy">
          </div>

          <div class="col-lg-6">

            <div class="position-sticky" style="top: 40px">
              <div class="portfolio-description">
                <h2>Overview</h2>
                <p>
                  Real-world scaled 3D CAD reconstruction of the Beit Hamikdash developed from image references, focusing on architectural accuracy and detailed structural representation for 3D printing.
                </p>

                <div class="portfolio-info mt-5">
                  <h2>Specifications</h2>
                  <ul>
                    <li><strong>Source:</strong> Image-based reference modeling</li>
                    <li><strong>Scaling:</strong> Real-world proportional reconstruction</li>
                    <li><strong>Scope:</strong> Full architectural model</li>
                    <li><strong>Application:</strong> 3D printing</li>
                  </ul>
                </div>

                <h2>Design Constraints</h2>
                <p>
                  <ul>
                    <li>Reconstruct complete structure from limited visual references</li>
                    <li>Maintain architectural proportions and layout consistency</li>
                    <li>Ensure geometry is suitable for 3D printing</li>
                    <li>Handle high model complexity across large-scale assembly</li>
                  </ul>
                </p>

                <div class="testimonial-item">
                  <p>
                    <h2>⭐⭐⭐⭐⭐</h2>
                    <i class="bi bi-quote quote-icon-left"></i>
                    <span>Really excellent work creating 3D models based on historical building models.</span>
                    <i class="bi bi-quote quote-icon-right"></i>
                  </p>
                  <div>
                    <!-- <img src="assets/img/person/person-f-5.webp" class="testimonial-img" alt=""> -->
                    <h3>Paris Lovett</h3>
                    <h4>Client</h4>
                  </div>
                </div>

                <h2>Design Approach</h2>
                <p>
                  The model was developed entirely from scratch using image references and historical visual data to reconstruct the full layout and structure.
                  <br><br>
                  Individual architectural elements were modeled and assembled to maintain proportional accuracy while ensuring print-ready geometry across the entire model.
                </p>

                <h2>Key Features</h2>
                <p>
                  <ul>
                    <li>Complete architectural reconstruction from reference images</li>
                    <li>Real-world proportional scaling across entire structure</li>
                    <li>High-detail modeling of walls, columns, and internal layout</li>
                    <li>Geometry optimized for large-scale 3D printing</li>
                  </ul>
                </p>

                <h2>Deliverables</h2>
                <p>
                <ul>
                  <li>Complete 3D CAD model of the full structure</li>
                  <li>Real-world scaled architectural reconstruction</li>
                  <li>Print-ready geometry for 3D printing</li>
                  <li>Structured model with all major components integrated</li>
                </ul>
                </p>

                <h2>Outcome</h2>
                <p>
                  Delivered a fully reconstructed and print-ready architectural model, accurately representing the structure and layout based on available visual references.
                </p>

              </div>

              <div class="portfolio-info mt-5">
                <h3>Project information</h3>
                <ul>
                  <li><strong>Category</strong>Client Project</li>
                  <li><strong>Client</strong>Paris Lovett</li>
                  <li><strong>Project date</strong>October, 2025</li>
                  <li><a href="https://www.upwork.com/freelancers/numanzamandipuu" class="btn-visit align-self-start" target="_blank">View Project on Upwork</a></li>
                </ul>
              </div>
            </div>

          </div>
        </div>

      </div>

    </section><!-- /Portfolio Details Section -->

    </main>

</BaseLayout>